name: Monumen Perjuangan Bhuwana Kertha
address: Jl. Ki Barak Panji, Panji, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: This is a WW2 memorial erected by the Dutch when they were ruling Indonesia. A good place for a picnic..but you need to bring own food as no warnings close by. This is also not far from Krishna park. Local public swimming pool and the Aling Aling waterfall. From this point follow the road to the left to go to Krishna an pool.. to take scenic drive that comes out in Anturan go to the right..
review 2: The best story in nort bali
review 3: Historical place to commemorate the heroes that passed away during the independence war in panji village buleleng regency
review 4: placed in a village, weather quite more hot than ubud..bit dusty
review 5: Nice place and must be visited! Many other spot nearby !
